dataIdInfo.idAbs: This polygon data layer represents tax parcels for Jackson County, Wisconsin in 2014. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Jackson_Parcels_2014.gdb. [Parcels of Jackson County, WI. The parcel layer was originally created in shapefile format by ProWest. They were imported to a feature class in Aug 2007. Features are based on deeds, surveys, and other legal documents. This dataset is updated continually as ownership and boundary lines change.]

attr.attrdef: - Unique number or identifier assigned to a parcel by the local GIS authority. The PARCELID is specific to GIS functionality and serves as the primary key to GIS joins or relationships. - This ID may have commonalities with the Tax Parcel ID. This ID may also be completely distinct from the Tax Parcel ID. - PARCELID for non-parcel features – If the attribute element’s geometry is not a parcel, then the PARCELID field may contain a label of the non-parcel feature.  PARCELID = BALSAM LAKE (to label a hydrography/lake polygon)  PARCELID = LAKE (to label a hydrography/lake polygon)  PARCELID = ROW (to label a street right of way polygon)  PARCELID = GAP (to label a gap in the parcel geometries) *Note that the above is not an exhaustive list of possible parcel feature labels

- Two letter state abbreviation of a parcel feature’s physical site address. - This is the state where the parcel itself is located (NOT the owner, whose mailing address in PSTLADRESS may be out-of-state).
- The calculated GIS parcel area, in acres, derived directly from GIS features. - GISACRES is calculated by the data contributor only. - GISACRES is optional and may be left <Null>.
